{"questionId":"23330068","questionHtml":"<p>Hence prove that the square of any integer can be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4t\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4t + 1\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\in {\\mathbb{Z}^ + }\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {4k} \\right)^2} = 16{k^2} = 4t\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {4k + 1} \\right)^2} = 16{k^2} + 8k + 1 = 4t + 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {4k + 2} \\right)^2} = 16{k^2} + 16k + 4 = 4t\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {4k + 3} \\right)^2} = 16{k^2} + 24k + 9 = 4t + 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mi>k</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>k</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>24</mn>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Hence, the square of any integer can be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4t\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4t&nbsp;+ 1\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\in {\\mathbb{Z}^ + }\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23330068","referenceCode":"EXM.1.SL.TZ0.1b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence prove that the square of any integer can be written in the form 4 t or 4 t + 1 , where t ∈ Z + .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}